  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "GLW is based on national census data downscaled to a spatial resolution of 5′ (or about 10 km at the equator) and allocated spatially using a set of suitability layers and other spatial predictors 50.",
    "Beyond GLW, there are few other livestock mapping efforts, excluding those that are highly localized.",
    "National livestock census data are key to efforts such as GLW, and although such data are available for many countries, their quality, resolution and timeliness are highly variable, and considerable efforts have to be expended on collation, harmonization and standardization before they can be used 53, 54.",
    "The date of census data collection is also highly variable: the census data in GLW version 4 ranges from the early 1990s to 2019, with all data at the pixel level being harmonized to the national-level FAOSTAT data for the years 2010 (GLW3) and 2015 (GLW4) 52.",
    "Other widely used global livestock datasets include the Global Livestock Production Systems (GLPS), the Global Environmental Assessment Model (GLEAM) 21, 55, 56 and the Herrero et al."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "GLW is based on national census data downscaled to a spatial resolution of 5′ (or about 10 km at the equator) and allocated spatially using a set of suitability layers and other spatial predictors 50.",
    "National livestock census data are key to efforts such as GLW, and although such data are available for many countries, their quality, resolution and timeliness are highly variable, and considerable efforts have to be expended on collation, harmonization and standardization before they can be used 53, 54.",
    "The date of census data collection is also highly variable: the census data in GLW version 4 ranges from the early 1990s to 2019, with all data at the pixel level being harmonized to the national-level FAOSTAT data for the years 2010 (GLW3) and 2015 (GLW4) 52.",
    "Other widely used global livestock datasets include the Global Livestock Production Systems (GLPS), the Global Environmental Assessment Model (GLEAM) 21, 55, 56 and the Herrero et al."
